# ===========================================
# Claude AI Development Frameworks
# ===========================================
# EDUCATIONAL NOTE: This section shows how AI-assisted development
# artifacts are typically managed in production projects.
#
# In a normal project, these would be ACTIVE (uncommented) because:
# - User stories are work-in-progress documents
# - AI handovers contain session-specific context
# - Reviews and analysis are temporal snapshots
#
# For THIS open-source demo, they're COMMENTED OUT so you can:
# - See real user stories that built this project
# - Understand the scruaim framework in action
# - Learn from actual AI pair-programming artifacts
# - Explore how systematic development works
#
# In your own projects, uncomment these lines:
# ===========================================

# Scruaim framework (user stories & backlog)
# --------------------------------------------
# Normally you'd hide work-in-progress stories:
# .claude/scruaim/**/*.md
# !.claude/scruaim/**/README.md
# !.claude/scruaim/**/INSTRUCTIONS.md
# !.claude/scruaim/**/STORY-REVIEW.md
# !.claude/scruaim/**/*.gitkeep

# AI Handovers (context preservation)
# ------------------------------------
# These preserve context between AI sessions:
# .claude/handovers/*.md
# !.claude/handovers/README.md

# AI Reviews (code analysis snapshots)
# -------------------------------------
# These are point-in-time analysis documents:
# .claude/reviews/**/*.md

# AI Analysis (architecture documentation)
# -----------------------------------------
# These are generated analysis documents:
# .claude/analysis/**/*.md

# ===========================================
# WHY THESE ARE VISIBLE IN THIS PROJECT:
# ===========================================
# This project serves as a TEACHING TOOL showing:
# 1. How to work systematically with AI tools
# 2. Real user stories from idea to implementation
# 3. The evolution of a project through stories
# 4. How AI and humans collaborate effectively
#
# The .claude/ folder is your window into the
# development process, not just the final code.
# ===========================================

# Any other Claude-specific files (keep these hidden)
.claude/cache/
.claude/context/
.claude/sessions/
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/**/*.local.*
.claude/**/*.personal.*

